commits.message: feat(phase2): implement insight & iteration - activity tracking & metrics
Add Filament dashboard widgets for job application tracking
Improves application event handling and metrics calculations
Adds PDF download functionality with profile filters
Refactors CV management into job applications feature
Improve Filament UI/UX with sections and better icons
Adds configuration files and improves dependencies
Set up a fresh Laravel app
style(ui): make header background fully transparent
fix(ui): remove sticky behavior and glass treatment from header
chore(ui): introduce muted professional color palette and tone down gradients
style(ui): unify header with background, remove border; upgrade feature cards to advanced glassmorphism
refactor(ui): remove diagonal mask, add rounded glass hero, adjust CTA heading copy
feat(ui): add advanced sections (process, templates, testimonials), floating badges, glass header, decorative background
feat(ui): improved welcome page design with gradient hero, enhanced feature cards and CTA

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Structure
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for this sub-feature explaining the fundamental structure of a CV in the system. Describe how the Cv model serves as the root entity with various related components through Eloquent relationships such as hasOne or hasMany. Explain the role of each section type (HeaderInfo, Summary, Skills, etc.) and how they are linked to the main CV. Document the database schema relationships, including foreign keys and cascading behaviors. Include examples from the Cv.php model showing relationship methods and from the migration files showing table structure. Address common issues such as handling missing required sections and maintaining data integrity across related models. Provide guidance on how to extend the CV structure with new section types.

wiki_catalogs.name: Job Application Data Model
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the JobApplication entity. Detail all fields including company_name, job_title, status, send_status, application_deadline, next_action_date, job_description, and last_activity_at. Explain the enum constraints for status (draft, pending, interviewing, offered, accepted, rejected, withdrawn) and send_status (draft, sent). Document the purpose of each field and its validation rules. Describe the database schema including indexes on status and next_action_date for performance optimization. Include the relationship with CV (belongsTo) and PDFSnapshot (hasOne). Explain the business rule that last_activity_at is auto-updated on any modification. Provide examples from the migration file showing column definitions and from the model showing Eloquent relationships. Address soft delete considerations and foreign key behaviors.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Entity
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the CV entity. Detail its role as the central container for professional information in the CV Builder system. Explain the database schema including fields like title, soft_delete timestamps, and relationships. Document the Eloquent relationships: hasOne to HeaderInfo, hasMany to Sections, and inverse relationships to JobApplications and CVVersions. Describe the cloning functionality that enables deep copying of all sections, skills, and formatting. Illustrate how soft deletes preserve historical data while removing from active views. Include examples from Cv.php showing the morphMany relationship to PDFSnapshots and the implementation of the clone method. Explain how the display_order field enables section reordering and how JSON fields store flexible content like skills arrays. Provide usage examples from the Filament resource showing form configuration and table columns.

wiki_catalogs.name: On-Demand PDF Export
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for this sub-feature focused on on-demand PDF export. Explain how the CvPdfController handles PDF generation requests by loading the CV with all related sections and rendering the 'cv.pdf' Blade template using Spatie Laravel-PDF. Document the filename generation logic using the CV slug and current date. Detail the PDF rendering process including A4 page formatting and direct browser download. Provide a code example from CvPdfController::download() showing the controller flow. Address common issues such as missing Tailwind styling in PDF output, font loading problems, and memory limits during PDF generation. Include configuration tips for optimizing PDF appearance and performance.

wiki_catalogs.name: Dashboard Widgets
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for this sub-feature focused on Filament dashboard widgets. Explain the purpose and implementation of each widget: ApplicationStatsOverview for displaying key metrics like total applications and interview count, ApplicationStatusChart for visualizing application status distribution using charts, ApplicationsNeedingAction for surfacing pending follow-ups, RecentApplicationsTable for quick access to latest applications, and CvStatsOverview for tracking CV usage and version statistics. Document how these widgets extend Filament\Widgets\StatsOverviewWidget and Filament\Widgets\ChartWidget, their data querying patterns using Eloquent, and integration with the admin dashboard. Include code examples showing metric definitions, chart datasets, and table columns. Address customization options such as colors, icons, and refresh intervals. Explain performance considerations when rendering widgets with large datasets and how caching strategies can be applied.

wiki_catalogs.name: MVC Architecture
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create architectural documentation for the MVC structure of the CV Builder application. Explain how the Laravel MVC pattern is implemented with clear separation between models, views, and controllers. Detail the role of each component: Models (Cv, JobApplication) managing data and relationships, Views (Blade templates) handling presentation, and Controllers (CvPdfController) orchestrating requests. Document the request lifecycle from route definition in web.php to controller handling to view rendering. Include examples of how form requests are processed and how data is passed between layers. Illustrate with a request flow diagram showing interaction between route, controller, model, and view. Address best practices followed in the implementation, such as thin controllers and rich models, and explain how this structure enhances maintainability and testability.

wiki_catalogs.name: Customizing Filament Resources
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for customizing Filament resources in the CV Builder application. Thoroughly explain how to modify existing forms, tables, and pages within Filament resources by extending their configuration in the respective Resource classes. Include concrete examples from the codebase such as modifying the CvForm schema or adjusting column visibility in CvsTable. Document the structure of Pages, Schemas, and Tables directories and their role in defining admin UI behavior. Explain how to add custom actions, bulk actions, and relationship managers. Address integration with existing models and proper service injection. Provide guidance on maintaining upgrade compatibility when extending core resources and organizing overrides for clarity. Include troubleshooting tips for common issues like form validation failures or table rendering errors.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV System Data Model
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the CV entity and its core attributes. Detail the fields in the cvs table including id, user_id, title, is_active, created_at, updated_at, and deleted_at (soft delete). Explain the purpose of each field and its data type. Document the relationship between Cv and its dependent components: hasMany CvVersion, hasOne CvHeaderInfo, hasMany CvSection, and belongsTo User. Describe how soft deletes are implemented and their impact on data visibility and recovery. Include usage patterns for activating/deactivating CVs and how the is_active flag influences application behavior. Provide examples of common queries such as retrieving active CVs or listing all versions. Address data integrity constraints and validation rules enforced at the model level.

wiki_catalogs.name: Automatic Snapshot Creation
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the automatic PDF snapshot creation workflow. Explain how the JobApplicationObserver listens for model events and triggers snapshot generation when the send_status transitions to 'sent'. Document the event-driven architecture and the role of Laravel's observer pattern in decoupling business logic. Detail the sequence: JobApplication save  observer detects status change  PdfSnapshotService::create() invocation  PDF generation and storage. Include code examples from JobApplicationObserver::updated() and PdfSnapshotService::create(), highlighting conditional logic and error handling. Address common issues such as observer not registering, race conditions, and handling cases where the associated CV is null or deleted. Provide debugging tips and logging recommendations.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Header Information
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the CvHeaderInfo data model. Explain its role in storing personal identification and contact details for a CV, including name, job title, email, phone, and location. Document the database schema fields, their data types, and constraints such as required fields and character limits. Describe the one-to-one relationship with the Cv model and how it is accessed through Eloquent. Include examples from the codebase showing how header information is populated via Filament forms (CvForm.php) and displayed in the PDF template (pdf.blade.php). Address validation rules applied during form submission and considerations for internationalization of contact data. Provide guidance on extending the model with additional fields like LinkedIn or portfolio links.

wiki_catalogs.name: Header Information
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for managing the Header Information section of a CV through the Filament admin interface. Explain how the HeaderInfoRelationManager handles the hasOne relationship with CvHeaderInfo and defines the form schema with personal details (full name, job title), contact information (email, phone, location), and social links (LinkedIn, GitHub, website). Document the two-column layout implementation and field validation rules such as email format and URL validation. Include code examples showing the form components and table display configuration. Describe how the record title is derived from the full_name attribute and how only one header record can exist per CV. Address common issues like duplicate entry prevention and validation error handling during creation. Provide best practices for maintaining consistent personal information across multiple CV versions.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Experience
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the CvExperience model. Detail the database schema including fields: id, cv_section_id, role, company, start_date, end_date, description, company_url, created_at, and updated_at. Explain the relationship with CvSection (many-to-one) and how it contributes to the overall Cv structure through the section hierarchy. Document data validation rules such as required fields (role, company, dates), date format constraints, and URL validation for company_url. Describe access patterns like retrieving chronological work history or filtering by current employment. Provide examples of how experience data is formatted in Blade templates for PDF generation, including date range formatting and URL rendering. Address common issues such as handling ongoing roles and data migration strategies for date field normalization.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Versioning
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive documentation for CV Versioning system. Document its purpose, implementation details, API interfaces, and integration patterns. Include practical examples and troubleshooting guidance.

wiki_catalogs.name: PDF Snapshots
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive documentation for PDF Snapshots system. Document its purpose, implementation details, API interfaces, and integration patterns. Include practical examples and troubleshooting guidance.

wiki_catalogs.name: Technology Stack
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for this section focused on the technology stack of the CV Builder application. Detail each component of the stack: Laravel v12+ as the backend framework providing MVC architecture and Eloquent ORM; Filament v4 for the admin interface with its resource, form, and table builders; Spatie Laravel-PDF for generating styled PDFs from Blade templates; Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling; Vite for frontend asset compilation; and SQLite as the default database. Explain the role of each technology in the system and how they integratesuch as how Vite compiles Tailwind and JavaScript assets, how Filament leverages Laravel's service container, and how Spatie Laravel-PDF renders Blade views with Tailwind styling. Include version compatibility notes, configuration patterns in Laravel config files, and best practices for extending the stack. Provide examples from package.json and composer.json to show script definitions and dependency management.

wiki_catalogs.name: Managing Sections
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for managing CV sections through the Filament admin interface. Explain how each section (Header Info, Summary, Skills, Experience, Education, Projects, References, Custom Sections) is managed via dedicated RelationManagers that define form schemas and infolist displays. Document the process of adding, editing, and reordering sections using drag-and-drop functionality where applicable. Include code examples from the RelationManagers showing form schema definitions and relationship configurations. Describe how section ordering is persisted in the database and how it affects PDF rendering. Address common issues such as validation errors during section creation and handling of duplicate entries. Provide best practices for maintaining consistent section data across multiple CVs.

wiki_catalogs.name: Application Status Workflow
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the job application lifecycle management. Explain the complete status workflow from draft to final outcome (accepted/rejected). Document how status transitions are implemented in the JobApplication model and enforced through form validation in JobApplicationResource. Describe the visual representation using badges in the Filament table and filterable dropdown in the form. Detail the business logic behind status progression and how it impacts other system behaviors. Include examples from the resource configuration showing status field setup and from the model showing any status-related methods. Address common user workflows such as bulk status updates and the implications of each status value on reporting and analytics.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Versioning System
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the CV versioning system. Explain its purpose in capturing snapshots of CVs at specific points in time, particularly when cloning or before significant changes. Document the database schema with fields for cv_id, snapshot_json (containing serialized CV state), created_at, and reason. Describe the Eloquent relationship where a CV hasMany CVVersions and a CVVersion belongsTo a CV. Illustrate how the snapshot_json field preserves the complete state including all sections and content. Provide examples from CVVersion.php showing the casts configuration for JSON attributes. Explain the workflow where cloning a CV automatically creates a version snapshot for historical tracking. Show how the Filament interface in CVVersionResource.php enables viewing and managing these snapshots. Address common use cases like comparing versions or restoring previous states, and discuss performance considerations for storing large JSON snapshots.

wiki_catalogs.name: PDF Snapshots
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for this sub-feature focused on persistent PDF snapshots. Explain the purpose of PDF snapshots as immutable records of CVs sent with job applications, including their role in audit trails and integrity verification. Describe how the PdfSnapshotService creates snapshots by generating PDFs from CV data, calculating SHA-256 hashes, and storing files in the local disk under 'pdf-snapshots/'. Document the PDFSnapshot model's database schema including job_application_id, cv_id, file_path, and hash fields. Explain the automatic creation workflow triggered when a JobApplication's send_status changes to 'sent' via the observer pattern. Detail the Filament resource interface for viewing and downloading snapshots, including hash verification functionality. Provide code examples from PdfSnapshotService::create() and the model definition. Address common issues like missing observers, null cv_id references, and storage permission errors.

wiki_catalogs.name: Keyword Coverage Analysis
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for this sub-feature focused on the KeywordCoverageService. Explain how the service analyzes a job description and compares it against a CV's content to identify missing keywords that could improve alignment with the role. Document the text processing logic, including keyword extraction, normalization, and matching algorithms. Describe the service interface, input parameters (CV content, job description), and output structure (coverage score, missing keywords). Provide concrete examples from the codebase showing how the service is invoked and how results are presented to users. Explain integration points with the Filament admin interface and potential use cases for improving CV effectiveness. Address limitations such as keyword stemming, synonym handling, and false positives. Include performance considerations for processing large volumes of text and suggestions for enhancing accuracy through configuration or extension.

wiki_catalogs.name: Service Layer Design
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create architectural documentation for the service layer in the CV Builder application. Detail the implementation and purpose of service classes (PdfSnapshotService, KeywordCoverageService) in encapsulating business logic. Explain how these services are injected into controllers and invoked to perform complex operations like PDF generation and keyword analysis. Document the methods exposed by each service, their parameters, return types, and error handling strategies. Provide code examples showing service usage in controllers. Describe the benefits of this pattern in decoupling business logic from HTTP concerns, improving testability, and enabling reuse across different parts of the application. Include a sequence diagram showing the interaction between controller, service, and external dependencies (e.g., Spatie Laravel-PDF). Address how services handle data validation, error logging, and integration with third-party packages.

wiki_catalogs.name: Adding New CV Section Types
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for adding new CV section types in the CV Builder application. Explain the process of creating new database migrations for custom section models, defining Eloquent relationships in the Cv model, and registering new relation managers in the CvResource. Use the existing CvCustomSection and CustomSectionsRelationManager as a reference implementation. Document how to design the database schema to support flexible content storage and ordering. Include instructions for creating corresponding models, factories, and seeders. Provide examples of adding a 'Certifications' or 'Publications' section with rich text support. Address data validation, content formatting, and integration with the PDF generation pipeline. Discuss performance considerations when rendering multiple section types and strategies for future extensibility.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Structure Components
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the CV structural components data model. Explain the purpose of CvSection as a container for ordered content blocks (Experience, Education, Skills, etc.) and its polymorphic relationship with specific section types. Document the CvHeaderInfo model storing personal details and contact information. Describe CvSummary for professional summaries and CvCustomSection for user-defined sections. Detail the fields in each table including position ordering, type discrimination, and content storage. Explain the migration sequence that first created standard sections then extended support for custom sections. Include examples of how sections are ordered and rendered in the final CV. Address data consistency when reordering sections and constraints on section content length or formatting.

wiki_catalogs.name: Snapshot Storage & File Management
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content on the storage mechanism for PDF snapshots. Explain how the PdfSnapshotService uses Laravel's filesystem abstraction to store generated PDFs in the 'pdf-snapshots/' directory under storage/app/. Document the configuration in filesystems.php for the local disk driver and how file paths are recorded in the PDFSnapshot model. Describe the file naming convention using timestamps and UUIDs to ensure uniqueness. Cover security considerations such as directory permissions, web accessibility, and protection against direct URL exposure. Include code examples showing file_put_contents usage, Storage::disk('local') interactions, and path resolution. Address common issues like disk space exhaustion, file permission errors, and migration strategies for moving to cloud storage.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Summary Section
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the CvSummary data model. Explain its purpose in storing the professional summary or objective statement at the top of a CV. Document the schema including the content field, character limits, and its one-to-one relationship with the Cv model. Describe how the summary is rendered in both the admin interface and the final PDF output. Include examples from the Filament resource configuration and blade templates showing content handling. Address rich text considerations, if any, and data sanitization practices to prevent XSS. Explain how the summary is cloned when duplicating a CV and any versioning implications.

wiki_catalogs.name: Professional Summary
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for managing the Professional Summary section of a CV through the Filament admin interface. Explain how the SummaryRelationManager handles a hasOne relationship via the sections table using CvSummary and implements a specialized table configuration that filters for section_type 'summary'. Document the textarea form component with 10-row height and required validation, and explain the custom create and edit actions that manage both CvSection and CvSummary records. Include code examples showing the closure-based form filling and data persistence logic. Describe how the summary content is displayed in the table with a 100-character limit and how only one summary entry is allowed per CV. Address common issues such as content truncation in the table view and proper error handling during summary updates. Provide best practices for writing effective professional summaries that align with job applications.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Project
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the CvProject model. Detail the database schema including fields: id, cv_section_id, title, description, url, created_at, and updated_at. Explain the relationship with CvSection (many-to-one) and its role in the CV's project portfolio section. Document data validation rules including required title and description, URL format validation, and content length constraints. Describe access patterns such as retrieving featured projects or filtering by external URL availability. Provide examples of how project data is rendered in the PDF template, including hyperlink embedding and responsive layout considerations. Address common issues like handling private projects without URLs and migration strategies for legacy data imports. Include performance considerations for large project collections and caching strategies.

wiki_catalogs.name: Getting Started
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for this section focused on setting up the CV Builder application locally. Provide step-by-step installation instructions including cloning the repository, installing PHP and Node.js dependencies via composer install and npm install, configuring the .env file with database and mail settings, running database migrations with php artisan migrate, and seeding sample data with php artisan db:seed. Include instructions for starting the development server using php artisan serve and compiling assets with npm run dev or npm run build. Document prerequisites such as PHP 8.2+, Node.js 18+, and SQLite or MySQL. Explain the purpose of key files like bootstrap/app.php for bootstrapping Laravel and routes/web.php for defining web routes. Provide troubleshooting tips for common setup issues like missing extensions, asset compilation errors, or migration failures. Include a quick tour of the main entry points such as /admin for the Filament dashboard and /cv/{id}/pdf for PDF generation.

wiki_catalogs.name: Cloning CVs
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the CV cloning functionality. Explain how the clone method in the Cv model duplicates a CV and all its related sections (HeaderInfo, Summary, Skills, Experience, etc.) while maintaining referential integrity. Document the recursive cloning process that traverses all relationships and creates new instances with updated timestamps and UUIDs. Include examples from the Cv.php model showing the clone() method implementation and from the test suite demonstrating expected behavior. Describe use cases such as creating variations of a CV for different job applications. Address common issues like incomplete clones due to missing relationships or validation failures. Provide performance considerations when cloning large CVs with many sections and suggest optimization strategies.

wiki_catalogs.name: PDF Snapshot Creation on Send
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create detailed documentation for the automated PDF snapshot creation when a job application is sent. Explain how the JobApplicationObserver listens for model events and triggers the PdfSnapshotService when send_status changes to 'sent'. Document the sequence: observer detects change  service generates PDF using current CV  stores file with SHA-256 hash  creates PDFSnapshot record. Include code examples from JobApplicationObserver showing the updated() method logic and from PdfSnapshotService showing the create() method implementation. Describe the file storage path pattern and hash verification process. Explain how the PDF snapshot is linked to both the job application and the CV version. Address error handling if PDF generation fails and security considerations for file storage.

wiki_catalogs.name: Job Application Lifecycle
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for the Job Application lifecycle. Define JobApplication as the core entity for tracking job pursuit activities, with key attributes like company, job_title, status, application_deadline, next_action_date, and job_description. Explain the status workflow: draft  sent  pending  interviewing  offer_received/rejected/withdrawn. Document the Eloquent relationships: belongsTo CV (the tailored CV used), hasMany PDFSnapshots (versions sent), and morphMany for application events. Describe the observer pattern implementation in JobApplicationObserver.php that automatically updates last_activity_at on model events. Illustrate how the job_description field enables keyword coverage analysis. Provide examples from the model showing attribute casting and relationship methods. Explain the business logic behind the 'Needs Attention' filter that surfaces applications with upcoming deadlines or pending follow-ups. Include usage patterns from the Filament resource showing form layout and table filters.

wiki_catalogs.name: PDF Configuration
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for PDF configuration options. Document how Spatie Laravel-PDF is configured in the Laravel service container, including default settings for paper size (A4), orientation, margins, and DPI. Explain how these settings are applied both in the CvPdfController for on-demand exports and in PdfSnapshotService for snapshot generation. Describe how to customize the PDF rendering process through configuration changes and Blade template modifications. Include guidance on preserving Tailwind CSS styling in generated PDFs and handling custom fonts. Provide examples of modifying PDF options like landscape orientation or different paper sizes. Address performance considerations when generating large PDFs and memory usage optimization.

wiki_catalogs.name: Filament Resource System
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create architectural documentation for the Filament resource system in the CV Builder application. Explain how Filament resources (CvResource, JobApplicationResource, etc.) abstract CRUD operations and provide an admin interface for managing domain models. Detail the structure of a Filament resource including form schemas, table definitions, pages, and relation managers. Document how resources are registered in the AdminPanelProvider and configured in filament.php. Explain the relationship between Filament resources and Eloquent models, and how custom schemas (CVVersionForm, JobApplicationForm) define data entry interfaces. Include examples of complex field configurations and relationship management through relation managers. Provide a component diagram showing the interaction between Filament components, resources, and underlying models. Address customization capabilities, extensibility, and performance considerations when working with large datasets.

wiki_catalogs.name: Extending the Service Layer
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for extending the service layer in the CV Builder application. Explain how to create new service classes to encapsulate business logic, following the pattern established by PdfSnapshotService and KeywordCoverageService. Document best practices for dependency injection, error handling, and logging within services. Include examples of creating a new service for integrating with external job boards or enhancing keyword analysis with AI suggestions. Show how controllers should interact with services and how to test service methods using PHPUnit or Pest. Address service reusability across different parts of the application and proper separation of concerns. Provide guidance on type hinting, method documentation, and managing service complexity as functionality grows.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Content Types
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the CV content types. Detail each table's structure: CvExperience (role, company, dates, description, company_url), CvProject (title, description, url), CvEducation (institution, degree, dates), and CvReference (name, position, contact). Explain how these models relate to CvSection and ultimately to Cv through the section relationship. Document additional fields added via migrations like URLs for projects and company websites. Describe common access patterns such as retrieving all experiences for a CV or filtering projects by URL availability. Include data validation rules and formatting requirements for date ranges and contact information. Provide examples of how this data is transformed during PDF generation.

wiki_catalogs.name: Integrity Verification & Hash Validation
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content on the integrity verification system using SHA-256 hashes. Explain how the PdfSnapshotService calculates a cryptographic hash of the generated PDF content before storage and saves it in the database alongside the file path. Document the verification process available through the Filament admin interface, where users can validate that the stored file matches its original hash. Describe the implementation of hash verification in PDFSnapshotResource's infolist component and potential use in audit trails. Include code examples from PdfSnapshotService::calculateHash() and the Infolist::make() configuration. Address common issues such as hash mismatches due to file corruption, encoding differences, and clock drift in distributed systems.

wiki_catalogs.name: Standard CV Sections
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the CvSection data model and its related standard section types. Explain how CvSection acts as a polymorphic container for ordered content blocks such as Experience, Education, Skills, Projects, and References. Document the schema fields including type, position, and morph relationships. Describe how each RelationManager in the Filament resources configures the interface for managing these sections. Include examples of how section ordering is preserved and updated via drag-and-drop in the admin panel. Detail the Eloquent relationships between Cv and its sections, and how they are rendered sequentially in the PDF output. Address data integrity during reordering operations and constraints on section content structure.

wiki_catalogs.name: Skills Section
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for managing the Skills section of a CV through the Filament admin interface. Explain how the SkillCategoriesRelationManager handles multiple skill categories through a hasMany relationship via the sections table using CvSkillCategory. Document the form schema with category_name input and a Repeater component for managing individual skills, including minimum item validation. Describe the display_order field implementation for section reordering and how the firstOrCreate pattern ensures proper section initialization. Include code examples showing the mutateFormDataUsing and using callbacks that manage the relationship between CvSection and CvSkillCategory. Explain the table display with comma-separated skills formatting and drag-and-drop reordering capability. Address common issues such as handling empty skill entries and maintaining category consistency across CVs. Provide best practices for organizing skills into meaningful categories that enhance keyword coverage.

wiki_catalogs.name: CV Education
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive data model documentation for the CvEducation model. Detail the database schema including fields: id, cv_section_id, institution, degree, field_of_study, start_date, end_date, gpa, created_at, and updated_at. Explain the relationship with CvSection (many-to-one) and its integration within the CV's education history section. Document data validation rules such as required institution and degree, date format constraints, and GPA range validation (0.0-4.0 or equivalent). Describe access patterns like retrieving highest degree first or filtering by graduation status. Provide examples of how education data is formatted in the PDF output, including date range presentation and academic credential formatting. Address common issues such as representing incomplete degrees and international qualification equivalencies. Include data migration considerations for legacy records and localization requirements.

wiki_catalogs.name: Core Concepts
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for this section focused on the fundamental concepts that underpin the CV Builder application. Define key entities: CV as a container for professional information with sections like experience, education, and skills; CVVersion as a snapshot of a CV at a point in time; JobApplication as a tracked application with status, deadlines, and follow-ups; and PDFSnapshot as a generated PDF version of a CV for a specific application. Explain the relationships between these modelssuch as a CV having many JobApplications and multiple CVVersions. Describe the purpose of service classes like PdfSnapshotService for generating and storing PDFs and KeywordCoverageService for analyzing alignment between CV content and job descriptions. Illustrate the lifecycle of a CV from creation to cloning and versioning. Use code examples from the models to show Eloquent relationships and accessors. Clarify how soft deletes work on CVs and how observers like JobApplicationObserver trigger actions on model events.

wiki_catalogs.name: Soft Delete and Restore
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the soft delete and restore functionality. Explain how the SoftDeletes trait is implemented in the Cv model and how it affects database records by setting the deleted_at timestamp instead of permanent deletion. Document the user interface in the Filament resource that allows users to delete and restore CVs through list actions. Include examples from the migration file showing the deleted_at column addition and from the CvResource.php showing the delete/restore actions configuration. Describe the impact on related models and how cascading soft deletes are handled. Address common issues such as restoring a CV with already-deleted related sections and provide solutions. Include best practices for managing deleted CVs and implementing retention policies.

wiki_catalogs.name: Needs Attention Filtering Logic
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop comprehensive content for the 'Needs Attention' filtering system. Explain the business logic defined in FR-003: applications need attention if next_action_date is overdue, send_status is draft, or status is pending/interviewing (excluding rejected/withdrawn). Document how this logic is implemented in the Filament resource's filter system using query scopes. Provide the exact code implementation showing the closure-based query construction. Include examples from testing scenarios that verify the filter works correctly with various combinations of status, dates, and send_status. Describe how this filter appears in both the job applications list and the dashboard widget. Address performance considerations with database indexing on relevant columns and common troubleshooting scenarios when applications don't appear as expected in the filter.

wiki_catalogs.name: PDF Snapshot Mechanism
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Develop detailed content for the PDF snapshot mechanism. Explain its dual purpose: enabling one-click PDF export of CVs and creating immutable records of exactly which CV version was sent to employers. Document the database schema with fields for job_application_id (nullable), cv_version_id (nullable), file_path, hash (for integrity verification), and created_at. Describe the Eloquent relationships: belongsTo JobApplication and optionally to CVVersion. wiki_overview.content:
<blog>
# Comprehensive Project Analysis: CV Builder Application

## 1. Project Introduction

The CV Builder is a Laravel-based web application designed to help users create, manage, and track job applications with professional CVs. The system provides a comprehensive interface for building customizable CVs, tracking job applications, and generating PDF snapshots of CVs for submission. 

**Core goals and objectives:**
- Enable users to create and manage multiple CV versions with different content sections
- Track job applications with detailed status management and follow-up reminders
- Generate PDF versions of CVs optimized for job applications
- Provide analytics and insights on application performance and CV usage

**Target audience:**
- Job seekers managing multiple applications
- Career professionals maintaining different CV versions for various roles
- Users who need to track application status and follow-up actions

## 2. Technical Architecture

### Component Breakdown

The application follows a Laravel MVC architecture with Filament as the admin panel framework. The core components include:

- **Models**: Represent the data structure with relationships between CVs, sections, and job applications
- **Filament Resources**: Admin interface components for managing data
- **Services**: Business logic encapsulation for PDF generation and keyword analysis
- **Controllers**: Handle HTTP requests and responses
- **Database**: SQLite with comprehensive migration history

### Design Patterns

The application implements several design patterns:

- **Repository Pattern**: Through Eloquent models and relationships
- **Service Pattern**: Business logic separated into service classes
- **Observer Pattern**: JobApplicationObserver for event-driven operations
- **Factory Pattern**: Laravel factories for test data generation

### System Relationships

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Client] --> B[Filament Admin Panel]
    B --> C[API Layer]
    C --> D[Business Logic]
    D --> E[Data Access]
    E --> F[(Database)]
    D --> G[PDF Generation Service]
    D --> H[Keyword Analysis Service]
    G --> I[File Storage]
```

### Data Flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[User Input] --> B[Filament Form]
    B --> C[Laravel Controller]
    C --> D[Eloquent Model]
    D --> E[Database]
    E --> F[Service Layer]
    F --> G[PDF Generation]
    G --> H[File Storage]
    H --> I[Download Response]
```

## 3. Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points
- `app/Providers/Filament/AdminPanelProvider.php`: Admin panel configuration and routing
- `routes/web.php`: Web application routes
- `public/index.php`: Application bootstrap

### Core Modules
- `app/Models/Cv.php`: Core CV model with relationships and cloning functionality
- `app/Services/PdfSnapshotService.php`: PDF generation and storage service
- `app/Filament/Resources/Cvs/CvResource.php`: Admin interface for CV management

### Configuration Approach
- `config/filament.php`: Filament admin panel configuration
- `composer.json`: Dependency management and scripts
- `database/migrations/`: Database schema definition

### External Dependencies
- `composer.json`: Laravel framework, Filament admin panel, and spatie/laravel-pdf
- `package.json`: Frontend dependencies managed through Vite

### Integration Points
- `app/Http/Controllers/CvPdfController.php`: PDF download endpoint
- `app/Services/KeywordCoverageService.php`: Job description analysis service

### Component Relationships

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Cv Model] --> B[Section Models]
    A --> C[JobApplication Model]
    A --> D[CVVersion Model]
    A --> E[PDFSnapshot Model]
    B --> F[Content Models]
    C --> E
    C --> G[PDFSnapshotService]
    H[KeywordCoverageService] --> C
    I[CvPdfController] --> J[PDF Generation]
    K[AdminPanelProvider] --> L[Filament Interface]
```

## 4. Key Features

### Functionality Overview

The CV Builder provides comprehensive functionality for CV management and job application tracking:

1. **CV Management**: Create, edit, and organize CVs with customizable sections
2. **Version Control**: Track changes through CV version snapshots
3. **Job Application Tracking**: Monitor application status and follow-up actions
4. **PDF Generation**: Create professional PDF versions of CVs
5. **Analytics**: Dashboard widgets showing application statistics

### Implementation Highlights

**CV Cloning with Versioning**: The application implements a sophisticated cloning mechanism that creates version snapshots before duplicating CVs, preserving historical states.

**Dynamic Section Architecture**: The CV structure uses a flexible section-based approach where each section can contain different types of content (summary, skills, experience, etc.).

**Application Status Tracking**: Comprehensive job application tracking with status filtering for items needing attention.

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Dashboard
    Dashboard --> CVManagement: Create/Edit CV
    Dashboard --> ApplicationTracking: Track Applications
    CVManagement --> PDFGeneration: Generate PDF
    PDFGeneration --> Download: Download CV
    ApplicationTracking --> Analytics: View Statistics
    Analytics --> Dashboard: Return
```

### Feature Architecture

```mermaid
erDiagram
    CV ||--o{ CV_VERSION : versions
    CV ||--o{ JOB_APPLICATION : applications
    CV ||--o{ PDF_SNAPSHOT : snapshots
    CV ||--|{ CV_SECTION : sections
    CV_SECTION }|--|| CV_SUMMARY : summary
    CV_SECTION }|--|| CV_SKILL_CATEGORY : skills
    CV_SECTION }|--|| CV_EXPERIENCE : experience
    CV_SECTION }|--|| CV_PROJECT : projects
    CV_SECTION }|--|| CV_EDUCATION : education
    CV_SECTION }|--|| CV_REFERENCE : references
    CV_SECTION }|--|| CV_CUSTOM_SECTION : custom
    JOB_APPLICATION ||--o{ PDF_SNAPSHOT : pdf_snapshot
```

Sources:
- [composer.json](composer.json)
- [AdminPanelProvider.php](app/Providers/Filament/AdminPanelProvider.php)
- [Cv.php](app/Models/Cv.php)
- [PdfSnapshotService.php](app/Services/PdfSnapshotService.php)
- [CvResource.php](app/Filament/Resources/Cvs/CvResource.php)
- [CvPdfController.php](app/Http/Controllers/CvPdfController.php)
- [KeywordCoverageService.php](app/Services/KeywordCoverageService.php)
- [filament.php](config/filament.php)
</blog>
